oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Penicillin Residues in Milk Following Subconjunctival Injection of Procaine Penicillin G
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Liljebjelke, K.
Warnick, L. D.
Witt, M. F.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Subconjunctival injection
keratoconjunctivitis
pencillin
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Subconjunctival injection of procaine penicillin G is used to treat infectious bovine keratoconjunctivitis. The purpose of this project was to find out how long pencillin can be detected in milk after a single 1 ml bulbar subconjunctival injection of procaine penicillin G.
